{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_013umm92r3KJS9uEEPqsmjjF","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Adds namespace to all resources.\n2\t# This must match the namespace defined in ../static-namespace/namespace.transformer.yaml\n3\tnamespace: openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator\n4\t\n5\t# Value of this field is prepended to the\n6\t# names of all resources, e.g. a deployment named\n7\t# \"wordpress\" becomes \"alices-wordpress\".\n8\t# Note that it should also match with the prefix (text before '-') of the namespace\n9\t# field above.\n10\tnamePrefix: multiarch-tuning-operator-\n11\t\n12\t# Labels to add to all resources and selectors.\n13\t#commonLabels:\n14\t#  someName: someValue\n15\t\n16\t# [WEBHOOK] To enable webhook, uncomment all the sections with [WEBHOOK] prefix including the one in\n17\t# crd/kustomization.yaml\n18\t# [CERTMANAGER] To enable cert-manager, uncomment all sections with 'CERTMANAGER'. 'WEBHOOK' components are required.\n19\t#- ../certmanager\n20\t# [PROMETHEUS] To enable prometheus monitor, uncomment all sections with 'PROMETHEUS'.\n21\t#- ../prometheus\n22\t\n23\t# [WEBHOOK] To enable webhook, uncomment all the sections with [WEBHOOK] prefix including the one in\n24\t# crd/kustomization.yaml\n25\t#- manager_webhook_patch.yaml\n26\t\n27\t# [CERTMANAGER] To enable cert-manager, uncomment all sections with 'CERTMANAGER'.\n28\t# Uncomment 'CERTMANAGER' sections in crd/kustomization.yaml to enable the CA injection in the admission webhooks.\n29\t# 'CERTMANAGER' needs to be enabled to use ca injection\n30\t\n31\t# the following config is for teaching kustomize how to do var substitution\n32\tapiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1\n33\tkind: Kustomization\n34\tresources:\n35\t- ../crd\n36\t- ../rbac\n37\t- ../manager\n38\t- ../webhook\n39\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc1e0fde-6ca7-4a4e-b741-3cd98dca56b7","uuid":"376fbc22-35a7-4b50-bee5-542501fe78a4","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:28:12.859Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment/config/default/kustomization.yaml","content":"# Adds namespace to all resources.\n# This must match the namespace defined in ../static-namespace/namespace.transformer.yaml\nnamespace: openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator\n\n# Value of this field is prepended to the\n# names of all resources, e.g. a deployment named\n# \"wordpress\" becomes \"alices-wordpress\".\n# Note that it should also match with the prefix (text before '-') of the namespace\n# field above.\nnamePrefix: multiarch-tuning-operator-\n\n# Labels to add to all resources and selectors.\n#commonLabels:\n#  someName: someValue\n\n# [WEBHOOK] To enable webhook, uncomment all the sections with [WEBHOOK] prefix including the one in\n# crd/kustomization.yaml\n# [CERTMANAGER] To enable cert-manager, uncomment all sections with 'CERTMANAGER'. 'WEBHOOK' components are required.\n#- ../certmanager\n# [PROMETHEUS] To enable prometheus monitor, uncomment all sections with 'PROMETHEUS'.\n#- ../prometheus\n\n# [WEBHOOK] To enable webhook, uncomment all the sections with [WEBHOOK] prefix including the one in\n# crd/kustomization.yaml\n#- manager_webhook_patch.yaml\n\n# [CERTMANAGER] To enable cert-manager, uncomment all sections with 'CERTMANAGER'.\n# Uncomment 'CERTMANAGER' sections in crd/kustomization.yaml to enable the CA injection in the admission webhooks.\n# 'CERTMANAGER' needs to be enabled to use ca injection\n\n# the following config is for teaching kustomize how to do var substitution\napiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1\nkind: Kustomization\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n","numLines":39,"startLine":1,"totalLines":39}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_015auKR17H7etWRxeEVeJ3Jm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the information needed. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-rule.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: multiarch-tuning-operator-alerts\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[10m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[10m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            message: >-\n              Image inspection failure rate has exceeded 5% over the last 10 minutes.\n              Pods may be stuck in SchedulingGated state or falling back to a default\n              architecture. Check image registry connectivity and pull secret\n              configuration.\n```\n\n## New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n  - prometheus-rule.yaml\n```\n\n## Key details\n\n- **Metric counters used**: `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` and `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` — both declared in `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go:58-69`.\n- **SLO threshold**: 5% failure rate (`> 0.05`) per `agentic/RELIABILITY.md:117` alerting table.\n- **Measurement window**: 10-minute `rate()` window, matching the PromQL example in `agentic/RELIABILITY.md:67-70`.\n- **`for: 5m`**: Requires the condition to persist for 5 minutes before firing, avoiding transient spikes.\n- **Severity**: `critical` — as specified in the RELIABILITY.md alerting thresholds table.\n- **Namespace `system`**: Matches the convention used by the existing ServiceMonitor in `config/prometheus/monitor.yaml:18`. Kustomize's `namespace` transformer in `config/default/kustomization.yaml` will rewrite this to `openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator`.\n\n## Commands\n\nNo `make` targets or code generation needed — this is a static YAML resource. To include it in a kustomize build, add `../monitoring` to the `resources` list in `config/default/kustomization.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\nTo validate the YAML:\n\n```bash\nkubectl apply --dry-run=client -f config/monitoring/prometheus-rule.yaml\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":695,"cache_read_input_tokens":41448,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":695,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc1e0fde-6ca7-4a4e-b741-3cd98dca56b7","uuid":"6fe357b3-9f91-46ca-adec-0c8d734afc3b","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:28:33.442Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDhmZmb3vDDwTUsUmUFx"}
